postcontent:
Brand new, not used
Remora IWB Holster
Series: 4ART
Fits: Keltec PF9/P11/P40, Ruger LC9, Beretta Nano, Sig P290, and other small framed semi-automatics and derringers.
*Sells for $47+ shipping brand new from Remora

If you are not familiar with Remora holsters, they are IWB holsters with a tacky outside material.  This allows you to place the holster in between your body and your pants with zero movement, zero printing, and no visible belt loop straps.  You can literally jump, run, crawl, and the holster will not move.  This particular model is tuckable (meaning there is a flap to tuck a shirt and still be able to draw quickly) with a detachable belt clip if you feel it necessary (it is not necessary).  I also opted for the leather lined model for a quick draw and the thinnest possible profile.

I purchased this with the intention of carrying while wearing formal business attire once the IL CCW license is made available.  However, I failed to realize that my company prohibits carrying on/near/during work.  As a result, I'm keeping my non-tuckable Remora holster for personal use and selling this one.

title: For Sale:  85.00
postcontent:
$85.00 takes all the knives.  Meet me to pick up everything.

4 assisted opening knives in brand new condition.

SOG Flash II Assisted Opening Knife Black Zytel (3.5" Black Serr) 
This Flash II (TFSA-98) has an AUS-8 stainless steel blade with a partially serrated edge and a black TiNi finish. The lightweight black glass-reinforced nylon handle is durable and features a diamond non-slip texture. 
The SOG Flash II represents super quality at an affordable price. Automatic knives not your thing? Try a spring assisted knife! As you push the thumb stud SOG's Spring Assisted Technology (S.A.T.) takes over and smoothly and quickly deploys the blade. The Flash II blade is easy to release from the open position with the sliding button on the handle that disengages the piston lock mechanism. Another great feature on the Flash II is the side mounted safety tab to prevent a misfire. The SOG Flash is a great EDC with a reversible pocket clip for tip-up carry.

CRKT Carson M16-12ZER Emergency Rescue Zytel Folding Tanto Knife (3" Satin Serr)
The Kit Carson designed CRKT M16-12ZER Emergency Rescue is a tough mid-sized every day carry (EDC) knife for emergency services with high visibility orange Zytel scales. The InterFrame handle has 420J2 stainless steel liners and CRKT's AutoLAWKS knife safety, which automatically actuates when the blade is open making it a virtual fixed blade. The handle has skeletonized black Zytel scales and a tip-down pocket clip. 
The CRKT M16-12ZER features a hollow ground Tanto style blade with a high satin finish and a partially serrated edge. The blade is easily opened with the dual thumb studs or a push of the Carson Flipper. The Teflon bearings at the blade pivot and an adjustable pivot screw allow for perfect blade action.

Boker Kalashnikov Automatic Knife Acid Green w/ Bowie Blade (3.35") satin plain.
This Kalashnikov knife features an exclusive bowie clip-point blade. This limited edition knife has satin finished blade, hardware and pocket clip. The AUS8 stainless steel blade holds a razor sharp blade and can tackle just about anything thrown its way. 
The ergonomically shaped handle is acid greenfinished aluminum with molded finger grips and jimping where the handle and blade meet. The design is thin, elegant and comfortable. The action of this knife is first rate. As with other Kalashnikov knives, this knife comes with a pocket clip for easy tip-up carry. 
Limited run, with serial number on blade. 

Boker Orange S2 Knife Sniper Bladeworks Folder (4" Plain) Limited Edition
This Boker S2 with Orange G-10 scales is a Blade HQ exclusive and limited to just 600 numbered pieces! Numbered 1/600, 2/600 etc. 
The S2 is a collaboration between Boker and Sniper Bladeworks. The knife was designed by Lance Abernathy, a former SWAT member, and features the handiwork of Jody Muller, knifemaker for the past 20 years. This team designs tactical folders of a slightly different kind. 
The S2 is unique due to its wide, completely flat ground 440C steel blade, which provides phenomenal cutting performance. The slim handle sits comfortably in your hand and guarantees perfect control. In addition, the thumb ramp and the flipper protect against slipping of the finger. The structured G-10 scales on steel plates offer maximum stability and a very secure grip. Also features an extra reversible pocket clip, which allows tip-up or tip-down carry, and the lanyard hole completes the package.



$85.00 will take the whole lot.

title: For Sale:  Spas12 Franchi Combat Shotgun Collectors Item Rare but Bad Ass home defense
postcontent: The Franchi SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun manufactured by Italian firearms company Franchi from 1979 to 2000. Only about 1,850 of the SPAS-12 shotguns manufactured were imported into the U.S. and that includes military/police and civilian use. Now about 89 these were changed to a fixed stock version with a smaller 6 round mag vs the pre 89 which were 8 round and collapsible stock. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 has been sold to military and police users worldwide, on the civilian market it has been featured in films, several video games and of course TV shows. The coolest feature is the ability to switch from pump to semi automatic. Now as far as military or police applications this allows lower impact rounds such as tear gas bean bags or rubber bullets which generally do not create enough gas pressure to cycle a round allowing the user the ability to manually extract and reload. But in civilian sector especially home defense mode this gun can be stored without a round in the chamber and as you are aware there isn't a criminal anywhere on earth that doesn't know the very distinct sound of a pump shotgun loading a round...... can you say asshole pucker effect. The coolest thing is that once you pump it once it can instantly be in semi auto so if you miss your target on the first shot the criminal may stick his stupid ass head up thinking you forgot to pump the shotgun to reload, bang he's dead. This has only been fired 20-25 times it has been in climate controlled storage in a gun safe since mid 80's this is the roughest toughest shotgun anywhere.
